# S01-T09: Error Boundary + Crash Recovery

## Objective
Implement React error boundaries with crash recovery for mission-critical HUD stability.

## Acceptance Criteria
- `src/app/ErrorBoundary.tsx` — Root error boundary with:
  - Fallback UI showing error details
  - Auto-retry mechanism (3 attempts with exponential backoff)
  - Error logging to console (extensible for remote telemetry)
- `src/shared/ui/WidgetErrorBoundary.tsx` — Per-widget error boundary:
  - Isolates crashes to individual HUD widgets
  - Shows minimal "Widget Error" placeholder
  - Does not crash entire HUD when one widget fails
- Global unhandled rejection/error handlers registered

## Steps
1. Create root ErrorBoundary class component
2. Create WidgetErrorBoundary for individual HUD slots
3. Register global error handlers in main.tsx
4. Add fallback UI with retry button
